urlhtml: Site of Jack the Ripper Murder 4
title: Site of Jack the Ripper Murder 4
description:
Catharine Eddowes Murder #4
Discovered @ 1.45 a.m.
Sunday, 30 September, 1888
Mitre Square
One of the nastiest of his five murders and happened on the same night as another murder. Having been disturbed and forced to run after murdering Elizabeth Stride elsewhere, he then committed another murder here. The victim's body had been badly mutilated and a kidney had been taken.
